Mini Search Engine (TF-IDF + Semantic Search + Autocomplete)

A fully functional search engine built from scratch — including a web crawler, inverted index, TF-IDF ranking, semantic search using MiniLM embeddings, and autocomplete using Trie, with a React UI front-end.

🚀 Live Links
Component	URL
Frontend	(after deployment)
Backend API	(after deployment)
🌟 Features
Feature	Description
Web Crawler	Crawls Wikipedia pages and extracts titles, text & images
Inverted Index	Maps keywords → documents
TF-IDF Ranking	Scores results based on keyword relevance
Semantic Search	BERT embeddings (MiniLM) for meaning-based search
Autocomplete	Trie-based prefix search suggestions
Search UI	Real-time search with suggestions & result cards
Image & Snippet Preview	Google-style view
Deployment	Backend on Render, Frontend on Vercel
🧠 Tech Stack
Backend

Python (Flask)

TF-IDF Ranking

Sentence Transformers (MiniLM)

BeautifulSoup / Requests (crawler)

Gunicorn (production)

Render deployment

Frontend

React.js

Live autocomplete

Highlighted keywords

Deployed on Vercel

